    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Selinum alatum are selinene, \u03b2-selinene oxide, selinol, \u03b1-selinene, and selinadiol, which are sesquiterpene compounds responsible for its medicinal properties. Selinene exhibits anti-inflammatory activity by inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes, such as COX-2 and LOX. \u03b2-Selinene oxide has been found to possess antimicrobial properties, effective against various pathogenic bacteria and fungi. \u03b1-Selinene has been reported to exhibit cytotoxic activity against cancer cells, while selinol has been shown to possess antioxidant properties, scavenging free radicals and protecting against oxidative stress. Additionally, selinadiol has been found to possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities, contributing to the overall therapeutic potential of Selinum alatum.",
