    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Selinum alatum are used to utilize its medicinal properties, which include tea infusion made by steeping dried leaves and flowers in hot water to treat digestive issues, tincture made by soaking the plant in a solvent to create a concentrated extract for pain relief, salve made by infusing the plant in a carrier oil to create a topical cream for skin irritations, infused oil made by steeping the plant in oil to treat muscle and joint pain, and decoction made by boiling the plant in water to treat respiratory issues. The tea infusion contains flavonoids and terpenoids, which are responsible for its medicinal effects. The tincture is often used to treat rheumatism and arthritis due to its analgesic and anti-inflammatory properties. The salve and infused oil are applied topically to treat skin conditions such as eczema and acne. Decoction is used to treat coughs and colds due to the presence of volatile oils and saponins in the plant.",
